Can you put these two remote call in the same try block, this "try" inside "try" seems confusing:
try {
      // serialization version is  introduced later than remoteVersion, have to call them in the right order
      remoteVersion = invoker.getRemoteVersion();
      remoteSerializationVersion = invoker.getRemoteGeodeSerializationVersion();
    }
    catch (Exception ex) {
      // if unable to get the remote version, we are certainly talking to a pre-1.5 cluster
      // if unable to get the remote serilization version, we are certainly talking to a pre-1.12 cluster
      gfsh.logInfo("failed to get the the remote version.", ex);
    }

